A semi-generic solution:

```css
:target {
    scroll-margin-top: ...;
}
```

This sets a `scroll-margin-top` for any link target (anchor/section). The value here must be the height of the overlapping element (e.g. navigation). This can be calculcated in SASS or using CSS `calc()` if necessary. Example from our project:

```scss
:target {
    scroll-margin-top: calc($brand-logo-height + $navbar-padding-y * 2);
}
```

So far I didn't find a solution to have this fully dynamic however.

