Following [Customize > Sass > Importing](https://getbootstrap.com/docs/5.2/customize/sass/#importing) you've got to include some of your instructions before the `maps` import.

Not tested but something like this:
```scss
@import '~bootstrap/scss/functions';
@import '~bootstrap/scss/variables';

$theme-colors: (
  'primary': $primary,
  'secondary': $secondary,
  'light': $light,
  'dark': $dark,
  'success': $success,
  'info': $info,
  'warning': $warning,
  'danger': $danger,
);

$custom-colors: (
  'custom': red,
);

$theme-colors: map-merge($theme-colors, $custom-colors);
$theme-colors-rgb: map-loop($theme-colors, to-rgb, '$value');

@import '~bootstrap/scss/maps';
// [...] Rest of the file
```

i've actually just given it a try in a branch, but the changes (to `_progress.scss`, `_spinners.scss`, and `_transition.scss`) end up being a bit more annoyingly repetitive than the suggested change above. taking the example in the OP, it would need to be (unless I'm mistaken)

```scss
@if $enable-transitions {
  @if nth($transition, 1) != null {
    transition: $transition;
    @if $enable-reduced-motion and nth($transition, 1) != none {
      transition: none;
      @media (prefers-reduced-motion: no-preference) {
       transition: $transition;
      }
    }
  }
}
```

similarly, in the others, you get the same dance, a la

```scss
@if $enable-transitions {
  .progress-bar-animated {
    animation: $progress-bar-animation-timing progress-bar-stripes;

    @if $enable-reduced-motion {
      animation: none;
      @media (prefers-reduced-motion: no-preference) {
        animation: $progress-bar-animation-timing progress-bar-stripes;
      }
    }
  }
}
```

```scss
@if $enable-reduced-motion {
  .spinner-border,
  .spinner-grow {
    --#{$prefix}spinner-animation-speed: #{$spinner-animation-speed * 2};
    @media (prefers-reduced-motion: no-preference) {
      --#{$prefix}spinner-animation-speed: #{$spinner-animation-speed};
    }
  }
}
```

considering that IE11 has now been officially sunsetted by MS for ages, that most browsers support the media query, and that users that DO require reduced motion at this point will likely transition to using a browser that actually provides them with this option that they need, I'd say the extra "define, then undefine, then redefine" dance required here is unnecessary and makes the SCSS more difficult to understand.
